    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You are talking about incrementing, while also settings the page parameter to the same value as it currently is. Once you set a parameter, the page is automatically reset to 0, since that would be the default behaviour once you apply a filter. A solution is to do the following:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst page = helper.state.page\r\nhelper.setQueryParameter('filters', 'date_timestamp:1538352000 TO 1540944000')\r\n  .setPage(page)\r\n  .search();\r\n```",
